sp_scores.title: Exploit the Chocobo Eater's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: The Chocobo Eater is vulnerable to fire, kupo! It has a powerful group attack, though, so bring along someone with a Soul Break that can heal the entire party!
tip_battle.title: Chocobo Eater

dungeons.epilogue: After fighting their way north along the Mi'ihen Highroad, Yuna and her party were prevented from advancing further by Yevon forces. Ahead in Mushroom Rock, Sinspawn gathered from throughout Spira were being used to bait out Sin as part of Operation Mi'ihen, a plan to use Al Bhed machina to defeat Sin once and for all. But it was not long before Maester Seymour arrived and invited Yuna's party to watch the battle from the headquarters of the operation.
dungeons.name: Mi'ihen Highroad
dungeons.prologue: Auron joins the party and together they make for Djose Temple. They travel along the Mi'ihen Highroad, but encounter an unexpected problem at its northern end...

sp_scores.title: Defeat Seymour without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: You won't be able to attack Seymour until you defeat the Guado Guardians, kupo! Once Seymour's HP drops low enough, he'll summon Anima. Anima's Defense is lower while it's gathering power, so time your attacks to hit then! Power Break and Magic Break also come recommended against Anima! After you defeat Anima, Seymour will use Doublecast, so have Shell and Reflect ready, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Seymour, Anima, & Guado Guardians

dungeons.epilogue: When the party confronted Seymour about the murder of his father, he confessed readily and tried to take Yuna from them by force. After a brutal battle, Seymour lay dead. Discovering his master's death, Tromell declared the party traitors and ordered them killed.
dungeons.name: Macalania Temple
dungeons.prologue: At the temple, Yuna and Seymour are already heading for the ceremony when the party learns that Seymour was responsible for murdering his own father, and rush to tell Yuna before it's too late.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Wendigo without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: You can Blind Wendigo to avoid his most powerful attacks, kupo! But if the Guado Guardians aren't taken care of first, they can remove Blind from Wendigo, so don't get cocky!
tip_battle.title: Wendigo & Guado Guardians

dungeons.epilogue: The party escaped from the temple, but were attacked on the frozen Lake Macalania and plunged through the ice. Beneath the water, they landed on a strange, submerged island that began to shake, revealing itself to be Sin. As Tidus's consciousness slipped away, he sensed that within Sin, his father Jecht still cared for Zanarkand.
dungeons.name: Macalania Lake
dungeons.prologue: Labeled traitors by Tromell after killing Seymour, Tidus and the others flee the temple.

sp_scores.title: Defeat ??? before he uses Jump.

tip_battle.message: ???'s true identity is Kimahri, kupo! Huh? You knew that already?

dungeons.epilogue: In Besaid, Tidus learns that his home of Zanarkand was destroyed one thousand years ago. He meets the summoner Yuna and accompanies her on her quest to defeat Sin. On their way to board a ship, they encounter the blue beastman, Kimahri Ronso, who joins them as another of Yuna's guardians.
dungeons.name: Besaid
dungeons.prologue: A group of blitzball players find Tidus washed ashore on a beach. He meets their captain, Wakka, who brings him to Besaid Village.

sp_scores.title: Defeat the Iron Giant without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: The Iron Giant hits with some pretty tough physical attacks, kupo. But it won't be so tough if you can Blind it!
tip_battle.title: Iron Giant

dungeons.epilogue: As they were nearing the end of the Thunder Plains, Yuna suddenly announced she would accept Seymour's offer, though she wouldn't explain her reasons for changing her mind. Though it didn't sit well with Tidus, the party agreed that, as long as she continued to fight Sin, the decision was hers to make.
dungeons.name: Thunder Plains
dungeons.prologue: Yuna and the others head for Macalania Temple, following Seymour after his sudden proposal to Yuna in Guadosalam. The party makes their way across the Thunder Plains.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Wendigo without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: You can Blind Wendigo to avoid his most powerful attacks, kupo! But if the Guado Guardians aren't taken care of first, they can remove Blind from Wendigo, so don't get cocky!
tip_battle.title: Wendigo & Guado Guardians

dungeons.epilogue: The party escaped from the temple, but were attacked on the frozen Lake Macalania and plunged through the ice. Beneath the water, they landed on a strange, submerged island that began to shake, revealing itself to be Sin. As Tidus's consciousness slipped away, he sensed that within Sin, his father Jecht still cared for Zanarkand.
dungeons.name: Macalania Lake
dungeons.prologue: Labeled traitors by Tromell after killing Seymour, Tidus and the others flee the temple.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Oblitzerator's weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: Attack the Oblitzerator with lightning abilities, its weakness, kupo! Whenever it's hit, it has a chance to counter with a debuffing attack, so be prepared. The Oblitzerator can be Paralyzed, though, so maybe you can use that to your advantage!
tip_battle.title: Oblitzerator

dungeons.epilogue: Yuna's kidnappers turned out to be members of an opposing blitzball team, the Al Bhed Psyches, who demanded the Besaid Aurochs throw their first match in exchange for her release. Fortunately, Tidus, Kimahri, and Lulu were able to board the Al Bhed ship where Yuna was being held and rescue her. Once Wakka and the other Aurochs learned she was safe, they rallied in the final minutes and defeated the Al Bhed Psyches.
dungeons.name: Luca
dungeons.prologue: The Besaid Aurochs have arrived in Luca for a blitzball tournament. As they wait for their match to begin, Yuna is kidnapped by the Al Bhed.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Lord Ochu's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: Lord Ochu does NOT like fire, kupo. But if you hit him with physical attacks, he has a chance to hit the entire party with his counter ability, Earthquake! Watch out!
tip_battle.title: Lord Ochu

sp_scores.title: Exploit Sinspawn Geneaux's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: Sinspawn Geneaux's tentacles deflect magic attacks directed at its body, kupo! Destroy the tentacles first, then go for the body! The body is vulnerable to fire, so turn up the heat!
tip_battle.title: Sinspawn Geneaux

dungeons.epilogue: The party encountered fiends left by Sin on the temple steps, but working together they defeated them. Wakka complimented Tidus on how he handled himself in battle, and for the first time Tidus considered becoming one of Yuna's Guardians. Within the temple they met the summoner Dona, who had no kind words for Yuna, but Yuna didn't rise to the bait. After passing the test within the Cloister of Trials, the party set out for Luca.
dungeons.name: Kilika Woods
dungeons.prologue: It's the day after Sin's attack on Port Kilika, and now Tidus and his party make for Kilika Temple.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Sinspawn Ammes without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Sinspawn Ammes's Gravity will take away a quarter of your current HP, kupo! Watch out for the Spines attack that usually follows after Gravity!
tip_battle.title: Sinspawn Ammes

dungeons.epilogue: Led by his childhood guardian Auron, Tidus approaches the gigantic sphere of water that Auron calls "Sin." Together they fight the Sinspawn that emerges and when Tidus reaches the sphere, he is drawn inside.
dungeons.name: Zanarkand
dungeons.prologue: Tidus is at the top of his game as star of the blitzball team the Zanarkand Abes. He is playing in the Jecht Memorial Cup tournament, when an immense creature attacks the city.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Sinspawn Gui without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Until you take down the arms, it's hard to get much damage through Sinspawn Gui's body. So go for the arms first, kupo! If its head starts moving suspiciously, it's getting ready to use its Venom ability. Use ranged attacks or magic to interrupt it!
tip_battle.title: Sinspawn Gui

dungeons.epilogue: Operation Mi'ihen had only just begun when Sin appeared near the shore. The Crusaders blasted it with cannon fire, while the Al Bhed fired off their machina gun, but neither seemed to have any effect, and Sin's backlash destroyed the gun. Auron then revealed to Tidus that Sin is none other than his father, Jecht, who wants Tidus to stop him.
dungeons.name: Mushroom Rock Road
dungeons.prologue: On the Mushroom Rock Road, the Crusaders have completed preparations, and are now ready to launch Operation Mi'ihen.

sp_scores.title: Defeat ??? before he uses Jump.

tip_battle.message: ???'s true identity is Kimahri, kupo! Huh? You knew that already?

dungeons.name: Besaid
dungeons.prologue: Tidus washes into the shallows off a beach where a practice game of blitzball is in session. He meets the team's captain, Wakka, who brings him to Besaid Village.

dungeons.name: Macalania Temple
dungeons.prologue: At the temple, Yuna and Seymour are already heading for the ceremony when the party learns that Seymour was responsible for murdering his own father, and rush to tell Yuna before it's too late.

sp_scores.title: Afflict Sinspawn Echuilles with Blind.

tip_battle.message: Did you know you can inflict Blind on Sinspawn Echuilles? It's true, kupo! Bring along abilities like Dark Attack or Dark Buster to turn out its lights!
tip_battle.title: Sinspawn Echuilles

dungeons.epilogue: As the party is en route to Port Kilika, Sin erupts from the waves, heading in the same direction as their ship. They attack it in an attempt to change its course. Though they manage to fight off the Sinspawn, Sin continues on heedless of their efforts, and Kilika is destroyed.
dungeons.name: S.S. Liki
dungeons.prologue: Wakka, the Black Mage Lulu, the Ronso Kimahri, and Tidus join Yuna on a ship for Kilika.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Chocobo Eater's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: The Chocobo Eater is vulnerable to fire, kupo! It has a powerful group attack, though, so bring along someone with a Soul Break that can heal the entire party!
tip_battle.title: Chocobo Eater

dungeons.name: Mi'ihen Highroad
dungeons.prologue: Auron joins the party and together they make for Djose Temple. They travel along the Mi'ihen Highroad, but encounter an unexpected problem at its northern end...

sp_scores.title: Defeat the Spherimorph without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: The Spherimorph uses Elemental Shift to change its elemental weakness and resistance, kupo! After the shift, it counterattacks with the opposite element of its new weakness! Fire and ice are opposites, and so are lightning and water, kupo. The Spherimorph only counterattacks when you hit it with the element it's resistant to, so attack with care!
tip_battle.title: Spherimorph

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Crawler's weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: When the Negator's on the battlefield, you can't use magic abilities or Soul Breaks, kupo! Take down the Negator first so you can use magic again, then attack the Crawler with its weakness, lightning!
tip_battle.title: Crawler & Negator

dungeons.epilogue: After they fought off the fiend in the spring, the party discovered a sphere left by Jecht in the water. Hearing from Auron that Jecht had sworn to battle Sin to the last, Tidus reaffirmed his dedication to their journey. After Yuna left for the temple with Seymour's butler, Trommel, the party was surrounded by Al Bhed. When Wakka learned that one of their attackers was Rikku's brother, a rift formed in the party's ranks, and Wakka headed off toward the temple alone.
dungeons.name: Macalania Woods
dungeons.prologue: On their way to Macalania Temple, Auron stops the party in Macalania Woods, taking them to a spring in the middle of the magical forest.

dungeons.name: Thunder Plains
dungeons.prologue: Yuna and the others head for Macalania Temple, following Seymour after his sudden proposal to Yuna in Guadosalam. The party makes their way across the Thunder Plains.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Extractor's weakness to lightning attacks.
Defeat the Extractor before it releases depth charges.

tip_battle.message: The Extractor attacks with dastardly Depth Charges, kupo! When it's getting ready to deploy them, melee attacks won't reach! If you hit it with lightning magic before it releases them, you can interrupt the Depth Charges, so get zapping!
tip_battle.title: Extractor

dungeons.epilogue: Tidus's party fought off the Al Bhed machina Extractor in the waters of the Moonflow. Across the river, they met Rikku, the Al Bhed girl Tidus met before coming to Besaid. At Yuna and Lulu's suggestion, they welcome her to the party as Yuna's sixth Guardian.
dungeons.name: Moonflow
dungeons.prologue: The Party leaves Djose Temple and is making their way across the Moonflow when Tidus spots ancient ruins beneath the waters, and they are attacked by Al Bhed.
